The term '''Hyuga Sandai''' refers to three of the five generations of earth deities in [[Japanese mythology|Japanese mythology]]: ''''[[Ninigi-no-Mikoto|Ninigi no Mikoto]]''', '''''Hiori no Mikoto'''' and ''''[[Ugayafukiaezu |Ugayafukiaezu]]''', and '''[[Ugayafukiaezu]]''', and the term refers to the three gods and their times. The [[Imperial House of Japan|Imperial House]] was founded in the [[Hyūga Province|Hyūga]]. It is generally located between the [[Tenson kōrin|Tenson's Descent]] and the [[Jinmu-Tōsaku]].

