{{Notability|date=June 2022}}The '''three generations of Hyuga''' refers to three of the five generations of earth deities in [[Japanese mythology]]: '''[[Ninigi-no-Mikoto|Ninigi no Mikoto]]''', [[Hoori|'''Hoori''' '''no Mikoto''']] and '''[[Ugayafukiaezu]]''',<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-08-04 |title=みやざきの神話と伝承101：概説 |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210804121336/https://www.pref.miyazaki.lg.jp/contents/org/chiiki/seikatu/miyazaki101/shinwa_densho/outline.html |access-date=2022-06-12 |website=web.archive.org}}</ref> and the term refers to the three gods and their times. The [[Imperial House of Japan|Imperial House]] was founded in the [[Hyūga Province|Hyūga]]. It is generally located between the [[Tenson kōrin|Tenson's Descent]] and '''{{ill|Jimmu's Eastern Expedition|ja|神武東征}}.'''

